      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here are the search results for the paper **\"Truth is Universal: Robust Detection of Lies in LLMs\"** by Bürger, Hamprecht, and Nadler, published at NeurIPS 2024:\n\n## Paper Overview\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The paper was authored by Lennart Bürger, Fred A. Hamprecht, and Boaz Nadler, and appeared in Advances in Neural Information Processing Systems 37 (NeurIPS 2024) Main Conference Track."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "It was published on September 25, 2024, and presented as a NeurIPS 2024 poster."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## Key Contributions\n\nThe paper addresses the problem of detecting when LLMs produce false statements. "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "LLMs are capable of \"lying,\" knowingly outputting false statements, and while several authors have trained classifiers to detect LLM lies based on internal model activations, other researchers showed that these classifiers may fail to generalise, for example to negated statements."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\nThe authors make the following key contributions:\n\n1. "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "They demonstrate the existence of a two-dimensional subspace along which the activation vectors of true and false statements can be separated. Notably, this finding is universal and holds for various LLMs, including Gemma-7B, LLaMA2-13B, Mistral-7B, and LLaMA3-8B."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n2. "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "They provided evidence for the existence of a truth direction tG that generalizes to unseen topics, unseen types of statements, and real-world lies, representing significant progress toward achieving robust lie detection."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## Resources\n\n- **NeurIPS Proceedings**: [proceedings.neurips.cc](https://proceedings.neurips.cc/paper_files/paper/2024/hash/f9f54762cbb4fe4dbffdd4f792c31221-Abstract-Conference.html)\n- **arXiv**: [arxiv.org/abs/2407.12831](https://arxiv.org/abs/2407.12831)\n- **OpenReview**: [openreview.net/forum?id=1Fc2Xa2cDK](https://openreview.net/forum?id=1Fc2Xa2cDK)\n- **Code & Datasets**: "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The GitHub repository at [sciai-lab/Truth_is_Universal](https://github.com/sciai-lab/Truth_is_Universal) contains the code and datasets necessary to reproduce the results."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- **Video Presentation**: [SlidesLive](https://slideslive.com/39028838/truth-is-universal-robust-detection-of-lies-in-llms)"
      }
